or datetime: YYYY-MM-DD[T]HH:MM[:SS[.ffffff]][Z or []HH[:]MM], e.g. 2024-01-01T00:00:00Z.

endpoints.description: Export a model config to a .prompt file by ID.

endpoints.name: Serialize
endpoints.description: Serialize a model config to a .prompt file format.

endpoints.name: Deserialize
endpoints.description: Deserialize a model config from a .prompt file format.

endpoints.name: List

queryParameters.description: String ID of project to return sessions for. Sessions that contain any datapoints associated to this project will be returned. Starts with `pr_`.
Page to fetch. Starts from 1.
Number of sessions to retrieve.

endpoints.description: Get a page of sessions.

endpoints.name: Create
endpoints.description:
Create a new session.

Returns a session ID that can be used to log datapoints to the session.

endpoints.name: Get

pathParameters.description: String ID of session to return. Starts with `sesh_`.

endpoints.description: Get a session by ID.

endpoints.name: Get Active Config

pathParameters.description: String ID of project. Starts with `pr_`.

queryParameters.description: Name for the environment. E.g. 'production'. If not provided, will return the active config for the default environment.

endpoints.description:
Retrieves a config to use to execute your model.

A config will be selected based on the project's
active config settings.

endpoints.name: Deactivate Config

pathParameters.description: String ID of project. Starts with `pr_`.

queryParameters.description: Name for the environment. E.g. 'production'. If not provided, will delete the active config for the default environment.

endpoints.description:
Remove the project's active config, if set.

This has no effect if the project does not have an active model config set.

endpoints.name: List Deployed Configs

pathParameters.description: String ID of project. Starts with `pr_`.

endpoints.description: Get an array of environments with the deployed configs associated to your project.

endpoints.name: Deploy Config

properties.description: Model config unique identifier generated by Humanloop.
List of environments to associate with the model config.

endpoints.description:
Deploy a model config to an environment.

If the environment already has a model config deployed, it will be replaced.

endpoints.name: Delete Deployed Config
endpoints.description:
Remove the version deployed to environment.

This has no effect if the project does not have an active version set.
